## Problem Statement
A small library needs a simple system to manage its books. The user (librarian) wants to add books, track copies, lend books to patrons, accept returns, and view current stock.

## Scope of the Project
- Console-based management of book inventory (no user accounts)
- Manage book title, author, available copies, and total copies
- Suitable for small college or community libraries
- Not designed for simultaneous multi-user access

## Target Users
- Small library staff or student librarians
- Beginners learning Python and basic software design

## High-level Features
- Add Book
- Borrow Book
- Return Book
- List Books
- Exit Application
